				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$P_{i} = d_{ijk} \sigma_{jk}$$\end{document}where Pi, dijk, and σjk represent the polarization vector, the piezoelectric third-rank tensor, and the stress tensor, respectively [94]. The piezoelectric third-rank tensor dijk comprises a piezoelectric matrix with typical values dependent on the specific crystalline structure. During a typical piezo-electro-chemical process, the piezoelectrically induced open-circuit voltage (Vi) follows the rule of piezoelectricity [27]:3Vi=dijkσjkwε0εr\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
