				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$f^{r} = \frac{x}{2l}\sqrt {\frac{E}{\rho }}.$$\end{document}

Equation (4) describes the resonance frequency (fr) of a typical rod vibrated longitudinally, where l, E, and ρ are the length, Young’s modulus, and density of the rod material, respectively. In addition, E is one of mechanical properties that define the relationship between stress and strain.5fr=11.2x2πl2EIρS.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
